"/> Possibly.

Did she pay with a credit card?

Sometimes stores can swipe the card and find a record of the
transaction in their database. Sometimes they will accept the fact
that their store appears on your monthly credit card statement with an
amount matching the item you purchased as prima facie evidence of your
purchase. Similarly, if she paid by check, a copy of the cancelled
check may suffice.

And some stores will simply take your wife's word for it.

</POST>



